Dear Dr. Strauss,

As requested, I am sharing the aggregated data from my counseling practice for your genetic-predisposition study.

• BRCA1 gene mutation (pathogenic or likely pathogenic variants): observed in approximately 5 % of the client population I counsel.

The figure above is based on de-identified, population-level data. No individual-level information or personally identifying details are included.

Please let me know if you would like the data in a different file format, if additional genetic markers would be helpful, or if you need any further clarification.

Best regards,
Jane
Genetic Counselor
